<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_ærwagæs_un" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><form type="lemma"><orth>ærwagæs un</orth><form type="variant"><orth>æragæs un</orth></form><form type="variant"><orth>iragæs un</orth></form></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>верить</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>to believe</q></cit></sense><re xml:lang="os-x-iron"><lang/><form type="lemma"><orth>wyrnyn</orth></form></re><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_ærwagæs_un." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>næ mi ærwagæs kænuj</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>я не верю</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>I don’t beleive</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Диг._сказ."/><biblScope>37</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>ba-di-ʼrwagæs wæd!</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>поверь!</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>believe!</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 129</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>osæj dær ba ʼragæs æj</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>женщина поверила</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>a woman believed</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>5%l10%l</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>kæmi mi barwagæs adtæjdæ!</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>где мне было поверить!</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>how was I supposed to believe!</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 42</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>kænæd di ærwagæs, kænʒænæj dæmæ eris</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>будь уверена, она будет с тобой спорить</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>be sure, she will argue with you</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/><biblScope>99</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>næ mi ærwagæs kænuj</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>я не верю</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>I don’t beleive</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Диг._сказ."/><biblScope>37</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>ba-di-ʼrwagæs wæd!</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>поверь!</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>believe!</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 129</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>osæj dær ba ʼragæs æj</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>женщина поверила</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>a woman believed</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>5%l10%l</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>kæmi mi barwagæs adtæjdæ!</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>где мне было поверить!</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>how was I supposed to believe!</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 42</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>kænæd di ærwagæs, kænʒænæj dæmæ eris</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>будь уверена, она будет с тобой спорить</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>be sure, she will argue with you</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/><biblScope>99</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Начальная дигорская группа %iærw%i- восходит обычно к %ivr%i-: <xr><ref target="#entry_ærwæz"/></xr> из *%ivraza%i-, %iærwæd%i (и. <xr><ref target="#entry_iræd"/></xr>) из *%ivrata%i; %iærwagæs%i могло получиться из %ivṛ%i- + %iākas-%i „казаться (%iākas%i-) верным (%ivṛ%i-)“, „принять за верное“. Ср. <xr><ref target="#entry_kæsyn"/></xr> в значении ‘казаться’, а для первой части — <xr><ref target="#entry_wyrnyn"/></xr> ‘верить’, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>вера</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="goh"><lang/><w>wār</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>verus</w></mentioned>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">The initial digor group %iærw%i- usually traces back to %ivr%i-:<xr><ref target="#entry_ærwæz"/></xr> from *%ivraza%i-, %iærwæd%i (Iron <xr><ref target="#entry_iræd"/></xr>) from *%ivrata%i; %iærwagæs%i could have been derived from %ivṛ%i- + %iākas-%i "to seem (%iākas%i-) true (%ivṛ%i-)", "to take something for a right thing". Compare <xr><ref target="#entry_kæsyn"/></xr> in the meaning ‘to seem’, and as for the first part — <xr><ref target="#entry_wyrnyn"/></xr> ‘believe’, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>vera</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="goh"><lang/><w>wār</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>verus</w></mentioned>.</etym></entry>